As MODIS 16-day EVI was composited from daily EVI maximum values throughout the year, it has noise emanated from outliers and cloud contamination. This noise was removed by using Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) technique. Fourier transform converts spatial domain image into frequency domain images (real frequency, imaginary frequency, and power spectrum frequency) by using forward transformation method. Then, noise free image was constructed by using filtered frequency domain images through reverse Fourier transform (Rocchini et al. 2013). Mathematically, the representation of Fourier transforms for discrete functions in two-dimensional space can be expressed as weighted sum of sines and cosines and it is given asFu,v=1NM∑x=0N-1∑y=0M-1fx,ye-2πiuxN+vyM\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
